OpenShift Setup 
What is OpenShift ?

OpenShift is basically Kubernetes + extra tools + easier management.
It helps you run containers in a more organized and secure way.

Basic Idea of Installation

What actually happens:

You prepare machines (VMs or physical servers)
Setup DNS + Load Balancer + Firewall
Create config files
Generate ignition files (these tell machines what to do)
Boot machines with RHCOS
Bootstrap node sets up the cluster
Remove bootstrap node
Workers join cluster
What You Need Before Starting
Machines

Minimum:

1 Bootstrap (temporary)
3 Master (control plane)
2 Worker

All machines run RHCOS

Simple sizing:
Master: 4 CPU, 16 GB RAM
Worker: 2 CPU, 8 GB RAM
Disk: at least 120 GB
Important Things (Don’t Ignore These)
1. DNS (VERY IMPORTANT )

If DNS is wrong → installation will fail.

You need:

api.cluster.domain
api-int.cluster.domain
*.apps.cluster.domain
records for all nodes (master, worker, bootstrap)

👉 Also reverse DNS (PTR) must work
If not → node will become localhost → install fails

2. Load Balancer

You must configure LB for:

API → port 6443
Machine config → 22623
Apps → 80 & 443

At start:

traffic goes to bootstrap + masters

Later:

only masters
3. Firewall

Allow ports like:

6443 (API)
22623
2379-2380 (etcd)
10250+
30000-32767
4789, 6081 (networking)
4. Time Sync (NTP)

All nodes must have correct time
Otherwise certificates will break

Installation Steps (Simple Flow)
Step 1: Prepare Installer Machine

Download:

OpenShift installer
oc command
Pull secret (from Red Hat)
Step 2: Create Config File

Create folder:

mkdir ocp-install
cd ocp-install

Create file:

vi install-config.yaml

Add basic info:

domain
cluster name
pull secret
ssh key
Step 3: Generate Files

Run:

./openshift-install create manifests

Then:

./openshift-install create ignition-configs

You will get:

bootstrap.ign
master.ign
worker.ign

👉 These files are VERY important

Step 4: Setup HTTP Server

Copy ignition files:

cp *.ign /var/www/html/

Start web server:

systemctl start httpd

Now nodes will download ignition from here

Step 5: Setup Load Balancer (HAProxy)

You configure HAProxy for:

API (6443)
Machine config (22623)
HTTP (80)
HTTPS (443)

👉 At start include bootstrap in config
👉 Later remove it

Step 6: Install RHCOS on Machines

Download RHCOS image
Boot each machine using it

Step 7: Configure Each Node

After boot:

Set network:

nmtui

Set timezone:

timedatectl set-timezone Asia/Karachi
Step 8: Install Using Ignition

Run on each node:

Bootstrap:
coreos-installer install --ignition-url=http://server/bootstrap.ign /dev/sda
Master:
coreos-installer install --ignition-url=http://server/master.ign /dev/sda
Worker:
coreos-installer install --ignition-url=http://server/worker.ign /dev/sda
Step 9: Wait for Bootstrap

On installer machine:

./openshift-install wait-for bootstrap-complete

👉 After done:

remove bootstrap from load balancer
Step 10: Finish Installation
./openshift-install wait-for install-complete
After Installation

Login:

export KUBECONFIG=auth/kubeconfig
oc get nodes
Adding New Worker Node

Just:

Boot new machine
Use worker.ign
Approve CSR (if needed)
oc get csr
oc adm certificate approve <csr>
Important Tips (From Experience)
DNS issues = 80% of failures
Always check reverse DNS
Load balancer config must be correct
Bootstrap must be removed after setup
At least 2 worker nodes should be healthy
Time sync must be correct
Simple Summary

👉 Ignition files = instructions for nodes
👉 Bootstrap = temporary installer node
👉 Masters = brain of cluster
👉 Workers = run apps
👉 DNS + LB = most critical parts
